Metadata: Niphatynes, methoxylamine pyridines from the marine sponge, "Niphates" sp

During recent studies of Fiji sponges, the authors repeatedly noticed that cytotoxic crude extracts afford unique natural products. This stimulated the investigation of an uncommon purple-blue sponge whose extract was toxic to P388 mouse leukemia at 25 ug/mL. Two monosubstituted pyridines were the novel components of this sponge and they are described in this paper.
